WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.245 --> 00:00:02.120
ALAN SEALES: Please
welcome Benjamin Scheuer.

00:00:02.120 --> 00:00:04.746
[APPLAUSE, CHEERS]

00:00:08.650 --> 00:00:11.340
The show, my gosh,
I saw it last week.

00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:14.550
It was absolutely amazing.

00:00:14.550 --> 00:00:17.130
It was like this
unexpected journey

00:00:17.130 --> 00:00:18.490
that I didn't expect to go on.

00:00:18.490 --> 00:00:22.010
I didn't have any
expectations going into it.

00:00:22.010 --> 00:00:24.350
But it's extremely personal.

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:27.730
Extremely, I guess, exposed,
for lack of anything else.

00:00:27.730 --> 00:00:29.730
Because you talk about
some very serious things,

00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:31.870
like happy and sad.

00:00:31.870 --> 00:00:35.769
But actually, happy and
sad is very obvious, yes.

00:00:35.769 --> 00:00:37.310
But I actually want
to read something

00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:39.700
from the website about the show.

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:42.870
It says a good storyteller
uses everything he has.

00:00:42.870 --> 00:00:46.250
So Benjamin Scheuer uses his
guitar, actually six guitars,

00:00:46.250 --> 00:00:49.910
in "The Lion," a wholly original
downtown musical experience

00:00:49.910 --> 00:00:52.230
that tells one man's
gripping coming-of-age story.

00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:54.730
The award-winning songwriter
inspires and disarms

00:00:54.730 --> 00:00:56.932
with his raw wit,
emotional depth,

00:00:56.932 --> 00:00:59.140
and leads you on a rock-and-roll
journey from boyhood

00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:01.790
to manhood through pain
and healing to discover

00:01:01.790 --> 00:01:04.319
the redemptive power of music.

00:01:04.319 --> 00:01:07.100
And that says it better
than obviously I ever could.

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:10.561
But would you mind
playing us a little song

00:01:10.561 --> 00:01:12.435
to get us started, the
beginning of the show?

00:01:12.435 --> 00:01:12.850
BENJAMIN SCHEUER: Sure.

00:01:12.850 --> 00:01:13.350
Yeah.

00:01:13.350 --> 00:01:15.360
This is how the show starts.

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:16.403
There's no introduction.

00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:23.816
My father has an old guitar
and he plays me folk songs.

00:01:23.816 --> 00:01:26.744
[MUSIC BENJAMIN SCHEUER, "COOKIE
 TIN BANJO"]

